title: Lazio Bodø / vs Glimt - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Quater Finals 2nd Leg
description: Lazio’s only previous meeting with Bodø/Glimt was in the 2-0 defeat in the first leg of this tie. They last hosted a Norwegian side back in October 2015, beating Rosenborg 3-1 in the UEFA Europa League. Bodø/Glimt are winless in all six of their European trips to Italy, drawing one and losing five. Their last away game in Italy was in a quarter-final second leg, losing 4-0 to Roma in the 2021-22 Conference League.

title: Athletic Club vs Manchester United - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Semi Finals 1st Leg
description: This is the first European meeting between Athletic Club and Manchester United since the 2011-12 UEFA Europa League last 16 – under Marcelo Bielsa, Athletic won both legs and eventually reached that season’s final. Manchester United have lost three out of four European matches against Athletic Club, with their one win coming back in February 1957 in the second leg of that season’s European Cup quarter-final, a 3-0 victory at Old Trafford which took them into the semi-final 6-5 on aggregate.

title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Bodø / Glimt - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Semi Finals 1st Leg
description: Tottenham Hotspur and Bodø/Glimt have never previously faced each other in any competition. Spurs have won all four of their previous European games against Norwegian teams, beating Lyn 6-3 and 6-0 in the 1972-73 UEFA Cup and Tromsø 3-0 and 2-0 in the 2013-14 UEFA Europa League. Bodø/Glimt have lost all three of their European meetings with English clubs, losing home and away against Arsenal in the 2022-23 UEFA Europa League, while they lost 3-2 away at Man Utd earlier this campaign in the group stages.

title: Arsenal vs PSG - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Semi Finals - 1st Leg
description: This will be the sixth meeting between Arsenal and Paris SG, while the Gunners are unbeaten across the previous five. Arsenal are the opponent that the French side have faced the most times in European competition without ever winning. Arsenal have already beaten Paris SG in the UEFA Champions League this season, winning 2-0 at the Emirates Stadium in the league phase last October. Only one English side have beaten Paris SG twice in a single edition of the competition: Manchester City in the 2020-21 semi-finals.

title: Manchester Utd vs West Ham Utd PL Summer Series - 2025 - Mini Match
Barcelona vs Internazionale - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Semi Finals - 1st Leg
description: Barcelona and Internazionale have faced each other on 16 previous occasions in Europe, with the Spanish side winning exactly half of those. They are winless in the most recent two, however, which came in the group stages of the 2022-23 UEFA Champions League. This will be just the second time Barcelona and Internazionale have met in the knockout stages of the European Cup/UEFA Champions League, with both coming precisely at the semi-final stage. The previous one – played in 2009-10 – saw Jose Mourinho’s Inter eliminate the reigning champions 3-2 on aggregate.

title: Manchester United vs Athletic Club - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Sime Finals 2nd Leg
description: In all major European competitions, only one side has ever won the first leg of a two-legged knockout tie away from home by 3+ goals and failed to progress, with Maccabi Tel Aviv doing so against Olympiakos in the 2023-24 UEFA Conference League last 16. In the five previous matches between Manchester United and Athletic Club, there have been 22 goals, with the Red Devils scoring 12 and conceding 10. All five of those matches have seen at least three goals scored.

title: Bodø / Glimt vs Tottenham Hotspur - UEFA Europa League 2024/25 - Sime Finals 2nd Leg
description: In the history of the UEFA Europa League since its rebrand ahead of the 2009-10 season, there have been 92 instances of a side winning the first leg of a knockout match on home soil by a 2+ goal margin, of which only nine have failed to progress in the overall tie. All eight prior semi-finalists to achieve the feat have progressed to the final. Across their major European history, Bodø/Glimt have lost all four of their matches against English opposition, including their only one on home soil vs Arsenal in October 2022. Each of the other three defeats have seen the Norwegian side concede exactly three goals.

title: Internazionale vs Barcelona - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Semi Finals - 2nd Leg
description: This will be the 18th major European meeting between Internazionale and Barcelona, with only Bayern Munich vs Real Madrid, Juventus vs Real Madrid and Inter vs Real Madrid played more often in history. Each of the last two games between the teams have ended 3-3, in the UEFA Champions League in October 2022 and this season’s first leg. Barcelona have won just one of their six away UEFA Champions League matches against Internazionale, a 2-1 win in December 2019. Overall, Barca have managed just five wins in 24 away games in Italy, their lowest win ratio in any non-Spanish nation in the competition.
